The paper deals with compressed sensing (CS) algorithms and their practical implementation with digital quantization of measurement data. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also presents a novel variational Bayesian inference based CS algorithm, which involves statistical modeling and estimation, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper deals with noise reduction and estimation, which falls under the signal processing (cs.SP) sub-category. The paper also involves simulations and comparisons with state-of-the-art methods, making it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with quantization error, which is a topic of interest in the statistical inference (cs.SI) sub-category.
